  "texts": [
    "Model agnostic meta-learning (MAML)MAML, one of the optimization-based approaches, allows the h parameters of the model to adapt quickly and easily to new tasks (classes).",
    "The initial h parameters of the model are adapted to new tasks with only a few examples in one or a few gradient steps.",
    "The difference from ProtoNet is that the model is fine-tuned for each episode in training and prediction is made by repeating the same process in testing.",
    "A diagram of the MAML algorithm is given in Fig. 3.The meta-training and meta-testing phases consist of episodes (tasks).",
    "The dataset for meta-training consists of episodes in the form of D train ¼ E 1; E 2;...; E n f gand each episode consists of a support and query set in the form ofE i ¼ S i; Q i f g.The MAML algorithm shown in Fig. 3 basically performs the computations for each episode in two stages:f h S i ð Þ ¼ Y S i; h i ¼ h À ar h L S i; Y S ið5Þf h i Q i ð Þ ¼ Y Q i; h ¼ h À br h L Q i; Y Q ið6ÞInitially, the parameters h are random values."
